						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 4) set up in the <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of Mahishāsuramardini temple.</p>						

						<p>Vīra-Ballāḷa III, 1334 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record refers to <hi rend="bold">Chikkāyi-Tāyi,</hi> the chief queen of <hi rend="bold">Hoyisaṇa Vīra Ballāḷadēva</hi> and to Vayijappa-daṇṇāyaka. It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1257, Bhāva, Dhanus [28], Vaḍḍavāra</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1334 A.D., December 24.</hi> All other details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
